'''Teun Koopmeiners''' ({{IPA|nl|tøːŋ ˈkoːpmɛinərs}}; born 28 February 1998) is a Dutch professional [[footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for {{Italian football updater|Juventus}} club [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] and the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands national team]].

Having represented the Netherlands at various youth levels, Koopmeiners was called up to the senior team's preliminary [[UEFA Nations League]] squad in August 2020.<ref name="KNVB Media">{{cite news |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/nieuws/nederlands-elftal/78151/voorlopige-oranjeselectie-bestaat-uit-32-spelers|title=Voorlopige Oranjeselectie bestaat uit 32 spelers|trans-title=Provisional Oranje squad consists of 32 players|date=19 August 2020|access-date=25 September 2020|work=KNVB Media|language=nl}}</ref> He was later part of their squad for the [[FIFA World Cup]] in [[2022 FIFA World Cup|2022]] and [[2026 FIFA World Cup|2026]].

==Club career==
===AZ===
[[File:Матч «Динамо» - АЗ 2-0. 15 сентября 2020 года — 1137461 (Teun Koopmeiners).jpg|left|thumb|Koopmeiners lining up for [[AZ Alkmaar|AZ]] in 2020|268x268px]]
Koopmeiners grew up in [[Castricum]], [[North Holland]], and took his first steps in football as a youth player for the local club, Vitesse '22.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.vitesse22.nl/nieuwsbericht/teun-koopmeiners-maakt-competitiedebuut-bij-az/ |title=Teun Koopmeiners maakt competitiedebuut bij AZ |date=3 October 2017 |newspaper=vitesse22.nl |language=Dutch |access-date=22 October 2019 |archive-date=2 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210802153319/https://www.vitesse22.nl/nieuwsbericht/teun-koopmeiners-maakt-competitiedebuut-bij-az/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> In 2009, he joined the [[AZ Alkmaar|AZ]] youth academy at under-12 level.<ref name="AZprofile">{{cite web|title=Spelerspagina van AZ|url=https://www.az.nl/nl/teams/spelers/az/teun-koopmeiners|website=az.nl|publisher=[[AZ Alkmaar]]|access-date=22 October 2019|archive-date=21 April 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210421020134/https://www.az.nl/nl/teams/spelers/az/teun-koopmeiners|url-status=dead}}</ref> He eventually progressed through the ranks, and as part of the club's reserve team, [[Jong AZ]], he became champion of the Dutch third division in the [[2016–17 Tweede Divisie|2016–17 season]], reaching promotion to the [[Eerste Divisie]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nu.nl/voetbal/4587372/jong-az-promoveert-jupiler-league-dankzij-titel-in-tweede-divisie.html |title=Jong AZ promoveert naar Jupiler League dankzij titel in Tweede Divisie |date=1 April 2017 |newspaper=nu.nl |language=Dutch |access-date=22 October 2019}}</ref>

On 18 August 2017, Koopmeiners made his professional debut for Jong AZ in a 3&ndash;1 away win over [[FC Den Bosch]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/481825|title=FC Den Bosch vs. Jong AZ – Football Match Report |publisher=ESPN |date=18 August 2017 |access-date=21 October 2019}}</ref> He made his first team-debut on 1 October, coming on as a substitute for [[Alireza Jahanbakhsh]] for the final 30 minutes of a 4&ndash;0 home loss to [[Feyenoord]].<ref>{{cite web|title=AZ vs. Feyenoord – 1 October 2017|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/10/01/netherlands/eredivisie/stichting-az/feyenoord-rotterdam-nv/2462397/|website=Soccerway}}</ref> At the end of the [[2017–18 Eredivisie|2017–18 season]], AZ ended in third place, and thereby qualified for [[2018–19 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]]. In his first professional season, he made 26 league appearances in which he scored one goal.<ref name="SW">{{cite web|title=T. Koopmeiners|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/teun-koopmeiners/399769/|website=Soccerway}}</ref>

On 1 March 2020, Koopmeiners played a 70-metre pass to set up [[Oussama Idrissi]] for AZ's second goal in a 2–0 win against [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] which put his side level on points with Ajax.<ref>{{cite web |title=Dank 70-Meter-Pass: Alkmaar holt Ajax in der Eredivisie ein |url=https://www.kicker.de/dank_70_meter_pass_alkmaar_holt_ajax_in_der_eredivisie_ein-771114/artikel |website=kicker |access-date=2 March 2020 |language=German |date=1 March 2020}}</ref> During the [[2019–20 AZ Alkmaar season]] Koopmeiners scored 16 goals in all competitions in 42 appearances,<ref>{{cite web |title=Games played by Teun Koopmeiners in 2019/2020 |url=https://www.soccerbase.com/players/player.sd?player_id=106199&season_id=152 |website=Soccerbase |access-date=25 September 2020 |date=25 September 2020}}</ref> helping his side finish second in the [[Eredivisie]] on goal difference behind the Champions [[AFC Ajax]].<ref>{{cite web |title=AZ Alkmaar's title chase is over but is this Europe's best academy?|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11912/11978634/az-alkmaars-title-chase-is-over-but-is-this-europes-best-academy |website=Sky Sports |access-date=26 August 2020 |date=25 September 2020}}</ref>

He scored his first goal of the [[2020–21 AZ Alkmaar season|2020–21]] season against [[Viktoria Plzen]] on 26 August 2020 in the [[UEFA Champions League]] qualifier 3–1 victory.<ref>{{cite web |title=Champions League qualifiers round-up: AZ Alkmaar survive scare to progress |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11945/12057421/champions-league-qualifiers-round-up-az-alkmaar-survive-scare-to-progress |website=Sky Sports |access-date=26 August 2020 |date=25 September 2020}}</ref> On 14 January 2021, Koopmeiners scored two goals, including an audacious backheel flick, to help his side clinch an 3–1 away victory against [[PSV Eindhoven]].<ref>{{cite web |title=AZ verslaat PSV in Eindhoven: 1-3 |date=13 January 2021 |url=https://www.rtlnieuws.nl/sport/voetbal/artikel/5208494/az-verslaat-psv-eindhoven-1-3 |publisher=RTL Nieuws |access-date=4 February 2021}}</ref>

===Atalanta===
On 30 August 2021, Koopmeiners signed for [[Serie A]] club [[Atalanta B.C.|Atalanta]] for a reported fee of €12&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://football-italia.net/official-koopmeiners-arrive-at-atalanta/ |title=Official: Koopmeiners arrive at Atalanta |last=Mork |first=Martin |date=30 August 2021 |publisher=Football Italia |access-date=3 September 2021}}</ref> He made his debut on 11 September in the home match against [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]], as a late substitute for [[Matteo Pessina]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Con la Fiorentina esordio di Koopmeiners |url=https://www.atalanta.it/news/con-la-fiorentina-esordio-di-koopmeiners/ |website=Atalanta |language=it-IT |date=12 September 2021}}</ref>

On 1 September 2022, Koopmeiners scored a [[hat-trick#Association football|hat-trick]] in a 3–1 Serie A victory over [[Torino F.C.|Torino]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://football-italia.net/serie-a-atalanta-3-1-torino-koopmeiners-hat-trick-takes-top-spot/ |title=Atalanta 3–1 Torino: Koopmeiners hat-trick takes top spot |last=Campanale |first=Susy |date=1 September 2022 |work=Football Italia}}</ref>

On 22 May 2024, he started in Atalanta's 3–0 victory over German champions [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] in the [[2024 UEFA Europa League final]].<ref name="=Atalanta win Europa League">{{cite web |last=Wilson |first=Jonathan |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/article/2024/may/22/atalanta-bayer-leverkusen-europa-league-final-match-report |title=Atalanta win Europa League as Lookman hat-trick ends Leverkusen's unbeaten run |work=The Guardian |date=22 March 2024 }}</ref>

===Juventus===
On 28 August 2024, Koopmeiners moved to fellow Serie A club [[Juventus FC|Juventus]], signing a five-year deal.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.juventus.com/en/news/articles/teun-koopmeiners-signs-for-juventus |title=Teun Koopmeiners signs for Juventus! |date=28 August 2024 |publisher=Juventus FC |access-date=28 August 2024}}</ref> The transfer fee paid to Atalanta was €51.3 million plus €3.4 million in "ancillary costs" as well as a further €6 million "upon the achievement of further performance objectives".<ref name="france24">{{cite news |title=Juve confirm Koopmeiners' big-money move from Atalanta |url=https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20240828-juve-confirm-koopmeiners-big-money-move-from-atalanta |access-date=28 August 2024 |work=France 24 |date=28 August 2024}}</ref>

On 1 September 2024, Koopmeiners made his first [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] appearance in a 0–0 draw with [[AS Roma]], replacing [[Juan Cabal]] at half-time.<ref>{{cite web |title=Juve held to goalless draw in tight encounter with Roma |url=https://www.juventus.com/en/news/articles/juve-held-to-goalless-draw-in-tight-encounter-with-roma-01-09-2024 |website=Juventus.com |access-date=5 September 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Koopmeiners made four appearances for the [[Netherlands national under-17 football team|Netherlands national under-17 team]],<ref name="OnsOranje">{{cite web|title=Koopmeiners Profile|url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/teams/184965/speler/298|website=[[Royal Dutch Football Association]]|access-date=23 July 2024|language=nl}}</ref> as well as two appearances for the [[Netherlands national under-18 football team|national under-18 team]]. As part of the [[Netherlands national under-19 football team|under-19s]], he played at the [[2017 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]], reaching the semi-finals and only losing to [[Portugal national under-19 football team|Portugal]]. At under-19 level, Koopmeiners made 13 appearances.<ref name="OnsOranje"/> After five appearances for the [[Netherlands national under-20 football team|Netherlands Under-20 team]],<ref name="OnsOranje"/> he made his debut for the [[Netherlands national under-21 football team|national under-21 team]] on 22 March 2018 in a 4&ndash;1 loss in [[Doetinchem]] to the [[Belgium national under-21 football team|Belgium U21]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Matchdata|url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/teams/185185/uitslagen/wedstrijd/30267|website=Royal Dutch Football Association|access-date=23 July 2024|language=nl}}</ref>

On 19 August 2020, Koopmeiners was called up to the senior [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands national team]] by caretaker manager [[Dwight Lodeweges]] in the preliminary squad for the [[UEFA Nations League]] fixtures against [[Poland national football team|Poland]] and [[Italy national football team|Italy]].<ref name="KNVB Media"/> The same year in October, he debuted in a friendly match against [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Mexico spoil De Boer debut with deserved win|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/soccer-friendly-nld-mex-report-idUKL8N2GY67P|website=[[Reuters]]|date=7 October 2020}}</ref> He made his competitive debut in a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification]] against [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]] on 7 September 2021, contributing with an assist in a 6–1 victory.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Netherlands 6-1 Turkey: Turkish delight for hat-trick hero Depay|url=https://www.dutchnews.nl/2021/09/netherlands-6-1-turkey-turkish-delight-for-hat-trick-hero-depay/|website=Dutch News|date=7 September 2021|access-date=23 July 2024}}</ref> Koopmeiners scored his first senior national team goal in a [[UEFA Nations League]] match against [[Wales national football team|Wales]] on 8 June 2022.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Koopmeiners schiet diagonaal de 1-0 binnen tegen Wales|url=https://nos.nl/collectie/13873/video/2431964-koopmeiners-schiet-diagonaal-de-1-0-binnen-tegen-wales|website=[[Nederlandse Omroep Stichting]]|date=8 June 202|access-date=23 July 2024|language=nl}}</ref> In the [[2022 FIFA World Cup|2022 World Cup]] quarter-final against [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]], known as the [[Battle of Lusail]], Koopmeiners assisted former AZ teammate [[Wout Weghorst]] with a clever free-kick routine in the 11th minute of stoppage time to send the fixture to extra time. He then scored his penalty in the subsequent [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|shoot-out]] but could not stop the Netherlands from being eliminated 4–3.<ref>{{cite web|title=World Cup: Argentina reach semi-finals after dramatic penalty-shootout win|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/live/football/61047818|website=[[BBC Sport]]|publisher=[[BBC]]|access-date=23 July 2024}}</ref>

On 29 May 2024, Koopmeiners was named in the Netherlands' squad for [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Netherlands Euro 2024 squad: Ian Maatsen dropped, Georginio Wijnaldum and Daley Blind retained|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5526712/2024/05/29/netherlands-euro-2024-squad-confirmed/|website=[[The New York Times]]|date=29 May 2024|access-date=7 June 2024}}</ref> However, he was forced to withdraw from the tournament squad after sustaining an injury during the warm-up for a friendly match against [[Iceland national football team|Iceland]] on 10 June 2024.<ref>{{cite news|first=Apollo|last=Hayes|title=Juventus target Koopmeiners ruled out of Euro 2024 through injury|url=https://football-italia.net/koopmeiners-ruled-out-euro-2024/|website=Football Italia|date=11 June 2024|access-date=11 June 2024}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Koopmeiners can play as a [[defensive midfielder]] or [[central midfielder]]. He can also play as a [[centre-back]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.football-oranje.com/the-50-eredivisie-u21-stars-to-watch-2018-19-teun-koopmeiners/|title=The 50 Eredivisie U21 Stars To Watch 2018/19: Teun Koopmeiners|date=5 August 2018|access-date=25 September 2020|work=KNVB Media}}</ref> He is known for his leadership qualities, and captained [[AZ Alkmaar]] despite his young age.<ref>{{cite web |title=Teun Koopmeiners, de geboren leider van AZ |url=https://www.volkskrant.nl/sport/teun-koopmeiners-de-geboren-leider-van-az~b6bae6f2/ |website=De Volkskrant |access-date=5 February 2021}}</ref>

==Personal life==
His younger brother [[Peer Koopmeiners|Peer]] is also a professional footballer; Peer still plays for [[AZ Alkmaar|AZ]].<ref>[https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/koopmeiners-grapt-over-broertje-door-jou-heb-ik-straks-een-voorletter-op-mn-rug Koopmeiners grapt over broertje: 'Door jou heb ik straks een voorletter op m'n rug!'] - Voetbal International {{in lang|nl}}</ref>

